ae. It is a perennial, rhizomatous herb with a height range of 50-120 cm. Its leaves are flat, linear, and 4-7 mm wide, with a glabrous and smooth surface, and are borne on a leafy stem. The plant produces brownish-yellow to greenish-brown spikes, 2.5-4.5 cm long, and is dioecious, meaning it has separate male and female plants. The fruit is a nutlet, 2-3 mm long, and is dispersed by wind.", "uses": "Carex bulgarica is a species of sedge that has been used in traditional medicine, particularly in Eastern Europe. Its medicinal properties are attributed to its rich content of flavonoids and phenolic acids. Carex bulgarica has been traditionally used to treat various health issues, including inflammation, fever, and digestive problems. Its anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties are thought to contribute to its medicinal benefits. Further research is needed to fully understand the potential health benefits of Carex bulgarica.", "taxonomy": "Carex bulgarica belongs to the family Cyperaceae, commonly known as the sedge family. Within this family, it is classified under the genus Carex, which comprises over 2,000 species of sedges. Carex bulgarica is further divided into several species and subspecies based on its physical characteristics and growth habits. The specific classification of Carex bulgarica is Carex \u00d7bulgarica, indicating it is a hybrid species. This classification is widely accepted by botanists and is used in various plant databases and classification systems.", "benefits": "Carex bulgarica is a species of sedge, but there isn't much information available about its specific health benefits. However, Carex bulgarica, like other plants in the Carex genus, is often used in traditional medicine to treat various ailments. Some potential benefits may include antioxidant and anti-inflammatory properties. These properties could be beneficial for reducing inflammation and improving overall health. Further research is needed to confirm the specific health benefits of Carex bulgarica.", "parts": "Carex bulgarica is a species of sedge that has been traditionally used in folk medicine in various parts of the world. The plant's rhizomes and roots are considered to be the medicinal parts, which are used to treat various health conditions. Carex bulgarica has been traditionally used to treat digestive issues, reduce inflammation, and relieve respiratory problems. The plant's extracts have also been studied for their potential antioxidant and antimicrobial properties. However, more research is needed to fully understand the medicinal properties and potential uses of Carex bulgarica.", "intro": "Carex bulgarica, also known as Bulgarian sedge, is a perennial plant species belonging to the family Cyperaceae. The plant has been traditionally used in folk medicine to treat various health issues, including respiratory problems, such as bronchitis and asthma, due to its anti-inflammatory and expectorant properties. The bioactive constituents of Carex bulgarica include flavonoids, phenolic acids, and terpenoids, which are responsible for its medicinal properties. The most common herbal preparations made with Carex bulgarica include infusions, tinctures, and decoctions, which are used to treat respiratory issues and promote overall well-being."}